    "name": "COU1: Tibial insert contact stress under physiological gait (Class II)",
    "description": "A finite element analysis model is used to predict peak contact stress distribution across the tibial insert articulating surface under ISO 14243-compliant gait loading profiles. Model influence is MEDIUM (experimental bench testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect stress predictions could lead to accelerated polyethylene wear and clinical failure). Model Risk Level 3.",
    "intendedUse": "Use FEA to identify peak contact stress locations and magnitudes across 6 gait-cycle loading configurations for a Class II UHMWPE tibial insert. Results compared against experimental pressure-sensitive film measurements and cadaveric strain gauge data using a normalized contact stress ratio (CSR < 1.15 acceptance criterion).",
